OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784510536
OL,3,CWho will get the big jobs in Burnham's
OL,4,Ccabinet?
OL,6,FThe stupidest game in politics is
OL,7,Fpredicting a new cabinet, because it
OL,8,Fis literally one person's call -
OL,9,FBurnham's tomorrow - and weirdly he
OL,10,Fhasn't shared his almost-decisions
OL,11,Fwith me.
OL,13,FAlso, even if - when he is PM tomorrow
OL,14,F- Burnham thinks he knows precisely
OL,15,Fwho he wants in which job, he'll be
OL,16,Faware that the picks of his
OL,17,Fpredecessors had an annoying habit of
OL,18,Fsaying "no thank you". Best laid
OL,19,Fplans, and all that.
OL,26,@zD@HOUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
