FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784510536
OL,3,CWho will get the big jobs in Burnham's
OL,4,Ccabinet?
OL,6,FThis could be some kind of economic
OL,7,Fgrowth council spanning Downing Street
OL,8,Fand the Treasury ` to compensate for
OL,9,FMahmood's lack of Treasury experience
OL,10,Fand economic expertise.
OL,12,FAs for foreign secretary, those close
OL,13,Fto Burnham think it will be Ed
OL,14,FMiliband, and that Yvette Cooper -
OL,15,Fcurrent incumbent - would return to
OL,16,Fbeing home secretary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784510536
OL,3,CWho will get the big jobs in Burnham's
OL,4,Ccabinet?
OL,6,FIt would be bizarre if Labour's deputy
OL,7,Fleader, Lucy Powell, didn't become
OL,8,Fdeputy prime minister, and if Louise
OL,9,FHaigh - so important to his elevation
OL,10,Ffrom Manchester mayor to PM - didn't
OL,11,Fbecome his chief enforcer as
OL,12,Fchancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster.
OL,14,FFinally, there is still loads of
OL,15,Fchatter that Ed Miliband's brother
OL,16,FDavid Miliband will return to
OL,17,Fgovernment from his self-imposed New
OL,18,FYork exile in some or other senior
OL,19,Fcapacity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784510536
OL,3,CWho will get the big jobs in Burnham's
OL,4,Ccabinet?
OL,6,FBut if he's not reprising his
OL,7,Ferstwhile role as foreign secretary,
OL,8,FGod knows what he will do.
OL,10,FCards on table. This could all be
OL,11,Fnonsense. But perhaps it is useful
OL,12,Fnonsense, because it is an insight
OL,13,Finto what senior members of Burnham's
OL,14,Fsoon-to-be-government think is likely.
OL,16,FAnd if they are wrong, that says
OL,17,Fsomething important about the
OL,18,Ftightness (lack of leakiness) of his
OL,19,Fcircle of trust.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
